"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-paris-olympics-what-to-watch-july-27-katie-ledecky-tough-first-test\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympics are fully underway, with competition in rugby, soccer, handball and archery having started before the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 138, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Saturday is officially considered Day 1, with many more sports in action and the first medals awarded.\", \"from\": 139, \"to\": 245, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Before the Games started, I shared myviewing guidewith a few things to check out each day of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 353, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll also be writing daily about the top events to watch, especially as story lines change throughout the Games.\", \"from\": 354, \"to\": 472, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To top it all off, I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll recap the action every day on theDaily Rings podcastwith Dan Gartland, where we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll hit on not just the biggest events, but everything you might have missed in some of the smaller sports as well.\", \"from\": 474, \"to\": 696, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 561, \"end\": 569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\", \"score\": 0.9999999895840119, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gartland\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s what I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll be watching Saturday, July 27.\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 749, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is not a comprehensive list;visit Olympics.comfor a full schedule.\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 822, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All events will stream live on Peacock.\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 862, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 854, \"end\": 861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9855619551357075, \"rank\": 0.012881219761450603, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I will also be tweeting out a schedule of medal events and Team USA games each day.\", \"from\": 864, \"to\": 947, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 923, \"end\": 931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999998098392279, \"rank\": 1.9016015895084556e-07, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"People liked when I made these for Tokyo, so let\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s do it again for Paris.\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 1024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 984, \"end\": 989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.671672975890435, \"rank\": 0.4888197517510515, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1018, \"end\": 1023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999840838, \"rank\": 1.5878206103713982e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s what I have my eye on Saturday, Day 1#Paris2024pic.twitter.com/7s4VecXMg9  Swimming is one of the most popular events in the Olympics every four years, and Day 1 at the aquatic center will see a few of the Olympics\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 most anticipated races.\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1275, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the highlights of the Tokyo Games was seeingU.S.\", \"from\": 1276, \"to\": 1331, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"legend Katie Ledeckygo back and forth with Australian Ariarne Titmus.\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1401, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1375, \"end\": 1385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9206324688776332, \"rank\": 0.08613007229961803, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They will square off in the 400-meter freestyle, a race Titmus won in Tokyo and at the 2023 world championships.\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1514, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1458, \"end\": 1464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 1472, \"end\": 1477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.671672975890435, \"rank\": 0.4888197517510515, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The field will also include 17-year-old Canadian Summer McIntosh, and all three swimmers have held the world record in this event at one point.\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1564, \"end\": 1579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Summer McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first session in the pool also includes both the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s and women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 4X100 freestyle relay, another marquee event.\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1780, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. relay team includes Caeleb Dressel, who won five gold medals in Tokyo buthas had a long road back to the Olympicsand did not qualify in the individual 100 free.\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1950, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1810, \"end\": 1824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caeleb Dressel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\"}, {\"begin\": 1854, \"end\": 1859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.671672975890435, \"rank\": 0.4888197517510515, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The finals start at 2:30 p.m.\", \"from\": 1952, \"to\": 1981, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET.\", \"from\": 1982, \"to\": 1985, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s water polo team is essentially a dynasty, having won three straight Olympic gold medals, as well as five world championships in the same time frame.\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2154, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The team took fifth at worlds in 2023 but rebounded for a gold at the most recent world championship in February.\", \"from\": 2155, \"to\": 2268, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The team starts its bid for another Olympic gold at 9:35 a.m.\", \"from\": 2270, \"to\": 2331, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET against Greece, which finished fourth at worlds in 2024.\", \"from\": 2332, \"to\": 2391, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2343, \"end\": 2349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.8893123547728327, \"rank\": 0.12446430546245436, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Several of the U.S. team\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s stars are back, including Maggie Steffens, who is playing in her fourth Olympics and already owns the record for most career Olympic goals.\", \"from\": 2393, \"to\": 2561, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2448, \"end\": 2463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maggie_Steffens\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Maggie Steffens\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maggie_Steffens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maggie_Steffens\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s competition is already mostly over, a scheduling oddity because both rugby sevens and track and field take place in the Stade de France.\", \"from\": 2563, \"to\": 2711, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2695, \"end\": 2710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA advanced to the quarterfinals but fell to Australia, meaning the team has two more games to determine a place between fifth and eighth.\", \"from\": 2712, \"to\": 2856, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2712, \"end\": 2720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999998098392279, \"rank\": 1.9016015895084556e-07, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2763, \"end\": 2772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9018881141163699, \"rank\": 0.10473813936665455, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The semifinals are South Africa vs. France (9:30 a.m.\", \"from\": 2858, \"to\": 2911, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2877, \"end\": 2889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\", \"score\": 0.922202835130189, \"rank\": 0.06715565186594641, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2894, \"end\": 2900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9999567681984599, \"rank\": 4.3233376062263914e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ET) and Fiji vs. Australia (10 a.m.\", \"from\": 2912, \"to\": 2947, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2920, \"end\": 2924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fiji_national_rugby_sevens_team\", \"score\": 0.9999978727328087, \"rank\": 2.127219867723332e-06, \"text\": \"Fiji\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fiji_national_rugby_sevens_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fiji_national_rugby_sevens_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2929, \"end\": 2938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9018881141163699, \"rank\": 0.10473813936665455, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ET).\", \"from\": 2948, \"to\": 2952, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Games last only 14 minutes, so tune in at the start time or you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll miss a good chunk of the action.\", \"from\": 2953, \"to\": 3054, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Losers of the semifinals will play for bronze at 1 p.m.\", \"from\": 3055, \"to\": 3110, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET, while the gold medal game starts at 1:45.\", \"from\": 3111, \"to\": 3156, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One fun quirk is that the gold medal game will actually be 20 minutes long (two 10-minute halves), despite the rest of the tournament being made up of shorter games.\", \"from\": 3157, \"to\": 3322, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fiji won gold in men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s rugby in both Olympics since the sport was introduced in 2016, the country\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s only two gold medals, in any sport, in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 3324, \"to\": 3483, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3324, \"end\": 3328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fiji_national_rugby_sevens_team\", \"score\": 0.9999978727328087, \"rank\": 2.127219867723332e-06, \"text\": \"Fiji\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fiji_national_rugby_sevens_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fiji_national_rugby_sevens_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Day 1 has a full slate of men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s basketball games, though the U.S. won\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t start until Sunday.\", \"from\": 3485, \"to\": 3580, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The game I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m most interested in on Saturday is Greece vs. Canada at 3 p.m.\", \"from\": 3581, \"to\": 3657, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3630, \"end\": 3636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.8893123547728327, \"rank\": 0.12446430546245436, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 3641, \"end\": 3647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999980613793615, \"rank\": 1.6769078498420689e-06, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ET, when Giannis Antetokounmpo makes his Olympic debut against a team stacked with NBA players.\", \"from\": 3658, \"to\": 3753, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3667, \"end\": 3688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giannis_Antetokounmpo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Giannis Antetokounmpo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giannis_Antetokounmpo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giannis_Antetokounmpo\"}, {\"begin\": 3741, \"end\": 3744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999998961056972, \"rank\": 1.0385767317174519e-07, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Beach volleyball will begin at one of the most scenic venues of these Olympics, situated right at the foot of the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 3755, \"to\": 3882, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two American teams will be in action: Miles Partain and Andy Benesh at 8 a.m.\", \"from\": 3883, \"to\": 3960, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3887, \"end\": 3895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999768568236117, \"rank\": 1.684056431750278e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ET against Cuba, and Kristen Nuss and Taryn Kloth at 4 p.m.\", \"from\": 3961, \"to\": 4020, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3972, \"end\": 3976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.9971658567104007, \"rank\": 0.0026812165224015137, \"text\": \"Cuba\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba_national_baseball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3982, \"end\": 3989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Forrester_family\", \"score\": 0.9856158918459986, \"rank\": 0.014594030263798689, \"text\": \"Kristen\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Forrester_family\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Forrester_family\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ET against Canada.\", \"from\": 4021, \"to\": 4039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4032, \"end\": 4038, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999980613793615, \"rank\": 1.6769078498420689e-06, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Sarah Bacon and Kassidy Cook will compete in the 3m springboard diving competition, an event in which they finished fourth at the world championships.\", \"from\": 4041, \"to\": 4204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4054, \"end\": 4065, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Bacon\", \"score\": 0.9999783626862015, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sarah Bacon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resou